-- PGA Championship Golf to Be Televised Partially in 3-D by Turner Sports
-- Barry Rothbard
-- 2010-07-28T18:49:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-28/pga-championship-golf-to-be-televised-partially-in-3-d-by-turner-sports.html

          
          
             Time Warner Inc.’s Turner Sports
said it will offer the first two days of this year’s PGA
Championship in 3-D.  
 The 92nd PGA Championship will take place Aug. 12-15 at
Whistling Straits Golf Club in Kohler, Wisconsin. 3-D coverage
will be offered on TNT during the first two rounds, from 3 p.m.-
7 p.m. New York time, and will feature the 12th and 17th holes,
both par 3s.  
 In April, CBS Corp.’s CBS and Disney Co.’s ESPN aired
portions of the Masters Tournament in 3-D.  
